00756 class SearchMatchIDLessThan {
00757    public:
00758       bool operator()(const SearchMatch& a, const SearchMatch& b) const {
00759          return a.getID() < b.getID();
00760       }
00761       bool operator()(const SearchMatch* a, const SearchMatch* b) const {

00765 
00766 class SearchMatchIDAndNameLessThan {
00767    public:
00768       bool operator()(const SearchMatch& a, const SearchMatch& b) const {
00769          if ( a.getID() != b.getID() ) {
00770             return a.getID() < b.getID();
00771          } else {
00772             return StringUtility::strcmp( a.getName(), b.getName() ) < 0;
00773          }
00774       }
00775       bool operator()(const SearchMatch* a, const SearchMatch* b) const {
00776          if ( a->getID() != b->getID() ) {
00777             return a->getID() < b->getID();
00778          } else {
00779             return StringUtility::strcmp( a->getName(), b->getName() ) < 0;
00780          }
00781       }
00782 };

02100 inline void
02101 SearchMatch::removeRegion( uint32 idx )
02102 {
02103    RegionMatchVector::iterator it = m_regions.begin();
02104    it += idx;
02105    if ( m_regions[idx].second ) {
02106       delete m_regions[idx].first;
02107    }
02108    m_regions.erase(it);
02109 }

02116 }
